3.3 Execute phase (FAST version)
roles/websphere_jvm_restart/tasks/execute_on_host.yml
What changed for performance
Cache install root once per host (only used when PID not found)
Group work by profile:
serverStatus.sh -all is run once per profile BEFORE and once AFTER (with one wait loop)
Banner is set once per host/owner (not per JVM)
---
- name: Initialize per-host tracking
  set_fact:
    jvm_results: "{{ jvm_results | default([]) }}"
    owners_touched: "{{ owners_touched | default([]) }}"
    cached_install_root: "{{ cached_install_root | default('') }}"
    cached_install_owner: "{{ cached_install_owner | default('') }}"

- name: Validate restart_requests exist
  assert:
    that:
      - restart_requests is defined
      - restart_requests is sequence
      - restart_requests | length > 0
    fail_msg: "No restart_requests on {{ inventory_hostname }}."

# ---- Cache install root once per host (used only when PID not found) ----
- name: Check install roots once per host
  stat:
    path: "{{ install_root }}"
  loop: "{{ was_install_roots }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: install_root
  register: install_root_stats

- name: Select first existing install root
  set_fact:
    cached_install_root: >-
      {{
        (install_root_stats.results
          | selectattr('stat.exists','equalto',true)
          | map(attribute='install_root')
          | list
          | first) | default('')
      }}

- name: Get install root owner (if root exists)
  when: cached_install_root | length > 0
  stat:
    path: "{{ cached_install_root }}"
  register: cached_root_stat

- name: Save cached install owner (fallback to ls if needed)
  when: cached_install_root | length > 0
  block:
    - set_fact:
        cached_install_owner: "{{ cached_root_stat.stat.pw_name | default('') }}"
    - when: cached_install_owner | length == 0
      block:
        - shell: "ls -ld {{ cached_install_root }} | awk '{print $3}'"
          register: cached_owner_cmd
          changed_when: false
        - set_fact:
            cached_install_owner: "{{ cached_owner_cmd.stdout | trim }}"

# ---- Group requests by profile (serverStatus per profile, not per JVM) ----
- name: Initialize profile_map
  set_fact:
    profile_map: {}

- name: Build profile_map {profile_name: [jvm1,jvm2,...]}
  set_fact:
    profile_map: >-
      {{
        profile_map
        | combine({ req_profile: (profile_map.get(req_profile, []) + [req_jvm]) })
      }}
  vars:
    req_profile: "{{ req_entry.profile_name }}"
    req_jvm: "{{ req_entry.jvm_name }}"
  loop: "{{ restart_requests }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: req_entry
    label: "{{ req_entry.profile_name }} -> {{ req_entry.jvm_name }}"

- name: Convert profile_map to list
  set_fact:
    profile_specs: "{{ profile_map | dict2items }}"

# ---- Process each profile sequentially (but host still parallel to other hosts) ----
- name: Process profiles on this host
  block:
    - name: Restart JVMs for one profile (batched serverStatus)
      include_tasks: restart_profile.yml
      loop: "{{ profile_specs }}"
      loop_control:
        loop_var: profile_spec
        label: "{{ env_name | default('na') }}:{{ inventory_hostname }} -> {{ profile_spec.key }} ({{ profile_spec.value | length }} JVMs)"
  always:
    - name: Cleanup banners (always)
      include_tasks: banner_cleanup.yml
      when: restart_banner_enabled | bool
roles/websphere_jvm_restart/tasks/restart_profile.yml
What this does

For ONE profile on ONE host:

Determine profile_bin + jvm_owner efficiently:
Try ps on JVMs until one is found (cheap loops)
If none running → use cached install root path mapping: <root>/profiles/<profile>
Set banner once per owner
Run serverStatus.sh -all once (pre)
Start STOPPED JVMs; restart STARTED JVMs (stop/kill/poll/start)
Run serverStatus.sh -all once in a wait loop until all JVMs are STARTED (post)
Record results for each JVM (success/failure)
Capture PID/cell via ps best-effort (only once per JVM after completion)
---
- name: Set profile vars for this batch
  set_fact:
    profile_name: "{{ profile_spec.key }}"
    profile_jvms: "{{ profile_spec.value | default([]) }}"

- name: Validate JVM list for profile
  assert:
    that:
      - profile_jvms is sequence
      - profile_jvms | length > 0
    fail_msg: "No JVMs provided for profile {{ profile_name }} on {{ inventory_hostname }}."

# --- Find a running JVM among the list to derive owner/path quickly ---
- name: Initialize ps_discovery variables
  set_fact:
    ps_found: false
    ps_words: []
    derived_from_ps: false

- name: Try ps discovery for JVMs (stop early when found)
  shell: "ps -ef | grep java | grep {{ discover_jvm }} | grep -v grep"
  register: ps_discover_cmd
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false
  loop: "{{ profile_jvms }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: discover_jvm
    label: "{{ profile_name }} -> ps check {{ discover_jvm }}"
  when: not ps_found
  ignore_errors: true

- name: Pick first matching ps line that ends with a JVM name in this profile
  set_fact:
    ps_discover_lines: >-
      {{
        (ps_discover_cmd.results | default([]))
        | map(attribute='stdout_lines')
        | list
        | flatten
        | select('match', '.*\\s(' ~ (profile_jvms | map('regex_escape') | join('|')) ~ ')$')
        | list
      }}
    ps_found: "{{ (ps_discover_lines | length) > 0 }}"

- name: If ps found, parse owner/pid/profile path rule (last 4 words)
  when: ps_found
  block:
    - set_fact:
        ps_words: "{{ ps_discover_lines[0].split() }}"
        jvm_owner: "{{ ps_words[0] }}"
        detected_config_path: "{{ ps_words[-4] }}"
        detected_cell_name: "{{ ps_words[-3] }}"
        detected_profile_name: "{{ ps_words[-2] }}"
        derived_from_ps: true

    - name: Validate profile name from ps matches current profile
      assert:
        that:
          - detected_profile_name == profile_name
        fail_msg: "ps-derived profile {{ detected_profile_name }} does not match payload profile {{ profile_name }}."

    - set_fact:
        profile_dir: "{{ detected_config_path | regex_replace('\\/config$', '') }}"
        profile_bin: "{{ (detected_config_path | regex_replace('\\/config$', '')) ~ '/bin' }}"

- name: If no ps found, derive profile paths from cached install root
  when: not ps_found
  block:
    - name: Ensure cached install root exists
      assert:
        that:
          - cached_install_root | length > 0
        fail_msg: "No running JVM found and no WebSphere install root found on {{ inventory_hostname }}."

    - set_fact:
        jvm_owner: "{{ cached_install_owner }}"
        detected_cell_name: "unknown"
        profile_dir: "{{ (cached_install_root | regex_replace('\\/$', '')) ~ '/profiles/' ~ profile_name }}"
        profile_bin: "{{ (cached_install_root | regex_replace('\\/$', '')) ~ '/profiles/' ~ profile_name ~ '/bin' }}"

    - name: Validate profile_dir exists
      stat:
        path: "{{ profile_dir }}"
      register: profile_dir_stat

    - assert:
        that:
          - profile_dir_stat.stat.exists
        fail_msg: "Profile path not found: {{ profile_dir }}"

# --- Banner ONCE per owner (not per JVM) ---
- name: Set host banner once for this owner
  when: restart_banner_enabled | bool
  include_tasks: banner_set_host.yml
  vars:
    banner_owner: "{{ jvm_owner }}"
    banner_summary: >-
      WebSphere JVM restart IN PROGRESS
      RITM: {{ ritm_number }}
      ENV: {{ env_name | default('na') }}
      Host: {{ inventory_hostname }}
      Profile: {{ profile_name }}
      JVMs: {{ profile_jvms | join(', ') }}

# --- serverStatus once BEFORE ---
- name: Run serverStatus.sh -all (pre)
  shell: "{{ profile_bin }}/serverStatus.sh -all"
  register: server_status_pre
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner }}"
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false

# Decide per JVM state from PRE status
- name: Build state lists from pre serverStatus
  set_fact:
    jvms_started_pre: "{{ jvms_started_pre | default([]) }}"
    jvms_stopped_pre: "{{ jvms_stopped_pre | default([]) }}"
  no_log: true

- name: Classify JVMs based on pre serverStatus
  set_fact:
    jvms_started_pre: "{{ jvms_started_pre + ([one_jvm] if started_hit else []) }}"
    jvms_stopped_pre: "{{ jvms_stopped_pre + ([one_jvm] if stopped_hit else []) }}"
  vars:
    started_hit: "{{ (server_status_pre.stdout | default('') | regex_search('ADMU0508I: The Application Server \"' ~ (one_jvm | regex_escape) ~ '\" is STARTED')) is not none }}"
    stopped_hit: "{{ (server_status_pre.stdout | default('') | regex_search('ADMU0509I: The Application Server \"' ~ (one_jvm | regex_escape) ~ '\" cannot be reached')) is not none }}"
  loop: "{{ profile_jvms }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: one_jvm
    label: "{{ profile_name }} -> classify {{ one_jvm }}"

- name: Ensure all JVMs are present in serverStatus output
  assert:
    that:
      - (jvms_started_pre | length) + (jvms_stopped_pre | length) == (profile_jvms | length)
    fail_msg: >-
      Some JVMs were not found or not classifiable in serverStatus output for profile {{ profile_name }}.
      Check naming or profile path.

# --- Actions: STOPPED -> start (fast) ---
- name: Start STOPPED JVMs
  shell: "{{ profile_bin }}/startServer.sh {{ stopped_jvm }}"
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner }}"
  changed_when: true
  loop: "{{ jvms_stopped_pre }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: stopped_jvm
    label: "{{ profile_name }} -> start {{ stopped_jvm }}"

# --- Actions: STARTED -> restart with safe stop/kill/poll/start ---
- name: Restart STARTED JVMs safely (stop timeout + kill -9 + PID poll)
  include_tasks: restart_started_jvm.yml
  loop: "{{ jvms_started_pre }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: started_jvm
    label: "{{ profile_name }} -> restart {{ started_jvm }}"
  vars:
    jvm_owner_for_restart: "{{ jvm_owner }}"
    profile_bin_for_restart: "{{ profile_bin }}"

# --- serverStatus once AFTER with a single wait condition for ALL JVMs ---
- name: Wait until all JVMs in this profile are STARTED (post)
  shell: "{{ profile_bin }}/serverStatus.sh -all"
  register: server_status_post
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner }}"
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false
  retries: "{{ restart_wait_retries }}"
  delay: "{{ restart_wait_delay }}"
  until: >-
    {{
      profile_jvms
      | map('regex_escape')
      | map('regex_replace', '^(.*)$', 'ADMU0508I: The Application Server \"\\1\" is STARTED')
      | map('regex_search', server_status_post.stdout | default(''))
      | select('!=', None)
      | list
      | length
      == (profile_jvms | length)
    }}

# --- Record results for each JVM (success if STARTED in post status) ---
- name: Record results for each JVM in this profile
  block:
    - name: Best-effort ps for pid/cell
      shell: "ps -ef | grep java | grep {{ result_jvm }} | grep -v grep"
      register: ps_after_jvm
      changed_when: false
      failed_when: false

    - name: Extract pid/cell best-effort
      set_fact:
        ps_lines: "{{ ps_after_jvm.stdout_lines | default([]) | select('match', '.*\\s' ~ (result_jvm | regex_escape) ~ '$') | list }}"
        new_pid: "{{ (ps_lines | length > 0) | ternary((ps_lines[0].split()[1]), 'not found via ps') }}"
        cell_name: "{{ (ps_lines | length > 0) | ternary((ps_lines[0].split()[-3]), (detected_cell_name | default('unknown'))) }}"
        started_ok: "{{ (server_status_post.stdout | default('') | regex_search('ADMU0508I: The Application Server \"' ~ (result_jvm | regex_escape) ~ '\" is STARTED')) is not none }}"

    - name: Append per-JVM result
      set_fact:
        jvm_results: >-
          {{
            jvm_results + [
              {
                'env_name': (env_name | default('na')),
                'env_host_profile_jvm': ((env_name | default('na')) ~ ':' ~ inventory_hostname ~ ':' ~ profile_name ~ ':' ~ result_jvm),
                'status': ( 'success' if started_ok else 'failed' ),
                'profile_dir': (profile_dir | default('unknown')),
                'cell_name': (cell_name | default('unknown')),
                'new_pid': (new_pid | default('')),
                'action': ( 'restart' if (result_jvm in jvms_started_pre) else 'start' ),
                'reason': ( '' if started_ok else 'Not STARTED after operations (post serverStatus)' )
              }
            ]
          }}
  loop: "{{ profile_jvms }}"
  loop_control:
    loop_var: result_jvm
    label: "{{ profile_name }} -> result {{ result_jvm }}"
roles/websphere_jvm_restart/tasks/restart_started_jvm.yml

This is the safe “restart” logic for a JVM that was STARTED:

stopServer async (won’t hang)
poll PID disappearance using ps -ef (awk by PID)
if still present after 10 min → kill -9 → poll again
verify PID gone → startServer
---
- name: Capture PID for stop/kill
  shell: "ps -ef | grep java | grep {{ started_jvm }} | grep -v grep"
  register: ps_for_kill
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false

- name: Extract pid_to_kill
  set_fact:
    kill_lines: "{{ ps_for_kill.stdout_lines | default([]) | select('match', '.*\\s' ~ (started_jvm | regex_escape) ~ '$') | list }}"
    pid_to_kill: "{{ (kill_lines | length > 0) | ternary((kill_lines[0].split()[1]), '') }}"

- name: Ensure PID is known for polling/kill
  assert:
    that:
      - pid_to_kill | length > 0
    fail_msg: "Cannot determine PID for {{ started_jvm }}; cannot enforce stop/kill."

- name: Stop server (async)
  shell: "{{ profile_bin_for_restart }}/stopServer.sh {{ started_jvm }}"
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
  async: "{{ stop_timeout_seconds }}"
  poll: 0
  changed_when: true

- name: Wait up to timeout for PID to disappear (ps polling)
  block:
    - name: Poll ps until PID disappears
      shell: "ps -ef | awk '$2=={{ pid_to_kill }} {print}'"
      register: pid_poll
      become: true
      become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
      changed_when: false
      failed_when: false
      retries: "{{ (stop_timeout_seconds // stop_check_delay) | int }}"
      delay: "{{ stop_check_delay }}"
      until: (pid_poll.stdout | default('') | trim) == ""
  rescue:
    - name: Kill -9 PID if still present
      shell: "kill -9 {{ pid_to_kill }}"
      become: true
      become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
      changed_when: true
      failed_when: false

    - name: Poll until PID disappears after kill -9
      shell: "ps -ef | awk '$2=={{ pid_to_kill }} {print}'"
      register: pid_poll_after_kill
      become: true
      become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
      changed_when: false
      failed_when: false
      retries: 60
      delay: 5
      until: (pid_poll_after_kill.stdout | default('') | trim) == ""

- name: Final verify PID is gone before start
  shell: "ps -ef | awk '$2=={{ pid_to_kill }} {print}'"
  register: pid_final_check
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false

- name: Assert PID is gone
  assert:
    that:
      - (pid_final_check.stdout | default('') | trim) == ""
    fail_msg: "PID {{ pid_to_kill }} still exists; will not start {{ started_jvm }}."

- name: Start server after confirmed stop
  shell: "{{ profile_bin_for_restart }}/startServer.sh {{ started_jvm }}"
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ jvm_owner_for_restart }}"
  changed_when: true
Banner tasks (host-level, once per owner)
roles/websphere_jvm_restart/tasks/banner_set_host.yml
---
- name: Determine banner owner home directory
  shell: "getent passwd {{ banner_owner }} | cut -d: -f6 || echo /home/{{ banner_owner }}"
  register: banner_owner_home_cmd
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false

- name: Set banner paths
  set_fact:
    banner_profile_file: "{{ (banner_owner_home_cmd.stdout | trim) ~ '/' ~ restart_banner_profile_filename }}"
    banner_status_file: "{{ (banner_owner_home_cmd.stdout | trim) ~ '/' ~ restart_banner_status_filename }}"

- name: Ensure .profile prints banner when status file exists
  blockinfile:
    path: "{{ banner_profile_file }}"
    create: true
    marker: "# {mark} {{ restart_banner_block_id }}"
    block: |
      if [ -f "$HOME/{{ restart_banner_status_filename }}" ]; then
        echo "############################################################"
        cat "$HOME/{{ restart_banner_status_filename }}"
        echo "############################################################"
      fi
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ banner_owner }}"

- name: Write banner status file (one write per profile batch)
  copy:
    dest: "{{ banner_status_file }}"
    mode: "0644"
    content: "{{ banner_summary }}\n"
  become: true
  become_user: "{{ banner_owner }}"

- name: Track owners touched for cleanup
  set_fact:
    owners_touched: "{{ owners_touched | union([banner_owner]) }}"
